How do you know?

67
00:06:13,265 --> 00:06:16,565
Well...

68
00:06:16,565 --> 00:06:20,465
Because I am also...

69
00:06:20,465 --> 00:06:22,965
Look at me.

70
00:06:22,965 --> 00:06:24,865
That's why.

71
00:06:26,165 --> 00:06:27,665
A bomb?

72
00:06:34,065 --> 00:06:36,065
I'm sorry, James.

73
00:06:36,065 --> 00:06:38,565
I haven't finished lunch yet.

74
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:42,965
Hey, just how long do you intend to spend on lunch, Jodie?

75
00:06:42,965 --> 00:06:44,965
Well, a lot of things have been happening

76
00:06:44,965 --> 00:06:47,565
and I'm still at the cafe on the basement floor.

77
00:06:47,565 --> 00:06:51,665
A lot of things? Any problem?

78
00:06:51,665 --> 00:06:54,065
No, it's nothing like that.

79
00:06:54,065 --> 00:06:57,465
Okay, after Camel comes out of the men's room,

80
00:06:57,465 --> 00:06:59,665
and I finish drinking my ice tea,

81
00:06:59,665 --> 00:07:01,865
we'll head on to join you there.

82
00:07:03,465 --> 00:07:05,465
I wonder, what's gotten into her?

83
00:07:05,465 --> 00:07:09,365
Jodie recently seems to have changed.

84
00:07:09,365 --> 00:07:12,265
Ever since the robbery, I think.

85
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:14,665
She told me not to tell James

86
00:07:14,665 --> 00:07:17,865
but I wonder what her concern about the black cap is?

87
00:07:27,865 --> 00:07:30,165
Hold... Hold it...

88
00:07:32,365 --> 00:07:34,165
Hold it there!

89
00:07:42,265 --> 00:07:45,465
That was... It can't be...

90
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:46,865
It can't be!

91
00:07:51,465 --> 00:07:52,865
Strange...

92
00:07:52,865 --> 00:07:56,065
If a man with a burn who can't talk comes to shop,

93
00:07:56,065 --> 00:07:59,265
I'm sure that one of the sales clerks should remember him.

94
00:07:59,265 --> 00:08:02,765
Does that mean that there was no such person in the first place?

95
00:08:02,765 --> 00:08:05,065
Then who was that guy that I saw?

96
00:08:09,065 --> 00:08:11,965
Shu?

97
00:08:11,965 --> 00:08:13,265
Sorry.

98
00:08:16,865 --> 00:08:18,765
Shu.

99
00:08:18,765 --> 00:08:21,465
Shu, is it you? It's you, isn't it, Shu?

100
00:08:21,465 --> 00:08:23,265
Tell me that it's you, Shu!

101
00:08:25,565 --> 00:08:27,665
What's it about?

102
00:08:29,465 --> 00:08:32,565
The edge of the coaster is bent.

103
00:08:32,565 --> 00:08:34,265
Was it bent to begin with?

104
00:08:38,765 --> 00:08:41,665
Get out of here! This area is dangerous.

105
00:08:44,265 --> 00:08:45,465
Shu!

106
00:08:49,565 --> 00:08:51,065
Shu!

107
00:09:01,565 --> 00:09:04,365
Why do you have something like that on your body?

108
00:09:04,365 --> 00:09:06,265
I have no idea!

109
00:09:06,265 --> 00:09:08,565
I was attacked from behind in the men's room and passed out.

110
00:09:08,565 --> 00:09:12,565
When I came, a masked man had wrapped this around me.

111
00:09:12,565 --> 00:09:15,265
That man told me

112
00:09:15,265 --> 00:09:18,165
to put paper bags in front of the escalator

113
00:09:18,165 --> 00:09:20,865
as well as in front of the stairs too, so I did.

114
00:09:20,865 --> 00:09:25,965
He threatened to set the bomb off if I didn't listen to him.

115
00:09:25,965 --> 00:09:27,465
At any rate, get the police!

116
00:09:27,465 --> 00:09:30,365
-Call the police, won't you... -No, you can't!

117
00:09:30,365 --> 00:09:32,065
Because he told me that the moment the police

118
00:09:32,065 --> 00:09:33,365
approached this department store,

119
00:09:33,365 --> 00:09:36,865
he would push the bomb switch to set it off!

120
00:09:36,865 --> 00:09:38,065
And of course,

121
00:09:38,065 --> 00:09:40,565
he told me that even if one person flees from this floor,

122
00:09:40,565 --> 00:09:42,065
that's it.

123
00:09:42,065 --> 00:09:44,765
No way... Can't be!

124
00:09:44,765 --> 00:09:47,765
What did the man want?

125
00:09:47,765 --> 00:09:50,265
He wanted to find

126
00:09:50,265 --> 00:09:55,365
the sender who puts of the 13 red T-shirts in this bag.

127
00:09:55,365 --> 00:09:58,165
He needs to be found at any cost.

128
00:09:58,165 --> 00:10:00,765
-Red T-shirts? -What?

129
00:10:00,765 --> 00:10:04,965
Yes. He said that...

130
00:10:04,965 --> 00:10:08,065
the sender is definitely on this floor!

131
00:10:08,065 --> 00:10:11,165
He's definitely on this floor?

132
00:10:14,965 --> 00:10:18,665
"Beika Department Store"

133
00:10:18,665 --> 00:10:21,065
Hey... Are you serious?

134
00:10:21,065 --> 00:10:24,865
He said that if he can't find the sender of the T-shirts,

135
00:10:24,865 --> 00:10:27,665
he's going to blow up the bomb?

136
00:10:27,665 --> 00:10:34,565
Yes. The masked man who wrapped the bomb around my body said so.

137
00:10:34,565 --> 00:10:39,365
Moreover, he tells you that the sender is on this floor too?

138
00:10:39,365 --> 00:10:41,165
Yes.

139
00:10:44,165 --> 00:10:46,265
He said that if the person turns up,

140
00:10:46,265 --> 00:10:49,865
he won't push the switch of the bomb.

141
00:10:49,865 --> 00:10:52,065
Hey! You heard what he just said, didn't you?

142
00:10:52,065 --> 00:10:53,665
I don't know what your problem is,

143
00:10:53,665 --> 00:10:56,765
but come out you, sender of the load of red T-shirts!

144
00:10:56,765 --> 00:10:59,165
If you're here, please come on out!

145
00:11:06,465 --> 00:11:08,765
I guess nobody's coming out.

146
00:11:08,765 --> 00:11:09,965
Yes.

147
00:11:09,965 --> 00:11:12,765
He was saying to turn off the escalators

148
00:11:12,765 --> 00:11:16,965
and to make sure that the elevator doesn't stop on this floor too.

149
00:11:16,965 --> 00:11:18,565
I see.

150
00:11:18,565 --> 00:11:20,365
He plans to keep all the people confined here

151
00:11:20,365 --> 00:11:25,065
until he finds the sender of the T-shirts.

152
00:11:25,065 --> 00:11:26,965
It can't be.

153
00:11:26,965 --> 00:11:28,965
No way, no darn way!

154
00:11:28,965 --> 00:11:30,365
Hey, hold it!

155
00:11:30,365 --> 00:11:32,665
Hold your horses! Hey!

156
00:11:34,665 --> 00:11:35,865
Calm down, hey!

157
00:11:35,865 --> 00:11:36,965
Everyone, calm down!

158
00:11:36,965 --> 00:11:38,465
Hey!

159
00:11:57,772 --> 00:12:00,372
Excuse me. Please stay on this floor.

160
00:12:02,472 --> 00:12:04,672
Calm down!

161
00:12:20,772 --> 00:12:22,972
You heard what he said, didn't you?

162
00:12:22,972 --> 00:12:24,172
The culprit is saying

163
00:12:24,172 --> 00:12:27,772
that he wants to find the one who send him the red T-shirts

164
00:12:27,772 --> 00:12:31,672
and that he's sure that the sender is here on this floor.

165
00:12:31,672 --> 00:12:35,372
He also saying that if anyone flees from this floor,

166
00:12:35,372 --> 00:12:37,372
he's going to switch the bomb on!

167
00:12:37,372 --> 00:12:40,572
Of course calling the police is the out of the question!

168
00:12:40,572 --> 00:12:44,372
Even if one person acts on his own, there's going to be victims.

169
00:12:44,372 --> 00:12:46,172
I mean, that's what he said, right?

170
00:12:46,172 --> 00:12:48,372
Yes.

171
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:54,772
Excuse me,

172
00:12:54,772 --> 00:12:57,972
but could you call the person in charge

173
00:12:57,972 --> 00:12:59,972
and have the escalators stopped

174
00:12:59,972 --> 00:13:03,472
as well as not make the elevators stop on this floor.

175
00:13:03,472 --> 00:13:07,372
-Yes, sir. -Of course not to use stairs too.

176
00:13:07,372 --> 00:13:12,372
Please make sure too that no one contacts the police!

177
00:13:12,372 --> 00:13:14,772
Because it is very likely that the culprit is here

178
00:13:14,772 --> 00:13:19,572
and watching everything that we're doing.

179
00:13:19,572 --> 00:13:21,372
All right.

180
00:13:23,872 --> 00:13:27,272
So, what are we going to do now?

181
00:13:27,272 --> 00:13:30,472
Why don't we take a look?

182
00:13:30,472 --> 00:13:32,072
At the mysterious red T-shirts

183
00:13:32,072 --> 00:13:35,772
that are being sent to him every week!

184
00:13:35,772 --> 00:13:37,772
What? Did I mention it?

185
00:13:37,772 --> 00:13:40,472
That they were being sent every week?

186
00:13:40,472 --> 00:13:45,872
A client who seems to know the bomb man asked us to do some checking.

187
00:13:45,872 --> 00:13:50,072
We were told by the person who red T-shirts sent to him every week,

188
00:13:50,072 --> 00:13:52,472
would come after noon to the sports goods floor

189
00:13:52,472 --> 00:13:55,472
of the Beika Department Store

190
00:13:55,472 --> 00:13:57,172
and would like me,

191
00:13:57,172 --> 00:13:59,672
Kogoro Mouri's help on the matter!

192
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:02,072
Kogoro Mouri...

193
00:14:02,072 --> 00:14:04,172
You mean that famous detective?

194
00:14:04,172 --> 00:14:06,072
Yes. That's why,

195
00:14:06,072 --> 00:14:13,172
I will find the sender of the red T-shirts and bomb man right away!

196
00:14:13,172 --> 00:14:16,772
Well, keep your distance and watch.

197
00:14:16,772 --> 00:14:18,272
Yes...

198
00:14:22,272 --> 00:14:23,572
What?

199
00:14:23,572 --> 00:14:26,172
A man with a burn scar on his right cheek

200
00:14:26,172 --> 00:14:28,372
left this store a while ago?

201
00:14:28,372 --> 00:14:30,472
Is that true?

202
00:14:30,472 --> 00:14:34,172
Yes. Right after you left to go outside

203
00:14:34,172 --> 00:14:37,472
to answer the call that you received.

204
00:14:37,472 --> 00:14:41,772
That man, wasn't he wearing a cap like this?

205
00:14:41,772 --> 00:14:44,472
Yes, he was.

206
00:14:45,572 --> 00:14:49,072
Is he Mr. Akai?

207
00:14:49,072 --> 00:14:52,472
I passed him in the men's room a while ago.

208
00:14:52,472 --> 00:14:56,172
With a man who looks exactly like Mr. Akai with a burn scar.

209
00:14:56,172 --> 00:14:59,372
No way! Is he here?

210
00:14:59,372 --> 00:15:03,272
Yes. I lost track of him, though.

211
00:15:03,272 --> 00:15:05,172
But, what brings him here?

212
00:15:05,172 --> 00:15:09,072
What? Then don't tell me that the person you said

213
00:15:09,072 --> 00:15:13,072
you saw during the bank robbery was...

214
00:15:13,072 --> 00:15:14,472
Yes, exactly!

215
00:15:14,472 --> 00:15:17,672
I was looking for him because he disappeared in the hustle and bustle

216
00:15:17,672 --> 00:15:18,972
after the case.

217
00:15:18,972 --> 00:15:23,372
Then I realized that the mark on the back of the cap

218
00:15:23,372 --> 00:15:27,372
was an original design by the Beika Department Store.

219
00:15:27,372 --> 00:15:30,872
So, I came down looking for a clue or something!

220
00:15:32,572 --> 00:15:34,072
I'm sorry.

221
00:15:34,072 --> 00:15:36,172
I wasn't too sure myself,

222
00:15:36,172 --> 00:15:38,372
so I couldn't tell any of the agents yet.

223
00:15:38,372 --> 00:15:42,072
Besides, it seems as though he lost his memory and can't talk,

224
00:15:42,072 --> 00:15:44,272
so I couldn't confirm anything either.

225
00:15:44,272 --> 00:15:46,072
You see...

226
00:15:46,072 --> 00:15:49,872
Is it possible that this is a trap that they set?

227
00:15:49,872 --> 00:15:51,172
What?

228
00:15:51,172 --> 00:15:53,572
You said so yourself too!

229
00:15:53,572 --> 00:15:55,772
That Shuichi Akai died!

230
00:15:55,772 --> 00:15:58,472
You also confirmed the fingerprints of the corpse, didn't you?

231
00:15:58,472 --> 00:16:00,172
There's no way that he's alive!

232
00:16:00,172 --> 00:16:01,972
But...

233
00:16:01,972 --> 00:16:06,972
The fingerprints of Conan and you were found,

234
00:16:06,972 --> 00:16:09,372
along with fingerprints of the man

235
00:16:09,372 --> 00:16:11,472
who burned to death a while ago.

236
00:16:12,872 --> 00:16:15,372
If it's Shu, I'm sure he'll do something about the situation!

237
00:16:15,372 --> 00:16:18,872
Besides, just what kind of trap do you propose this to be?

238
00:16:18,872 --> 00:16:22,972
Well... maybe they're up to something

239
00:16:22,972 --> 00:16:25,972
and trying to throw us off by confusing us.

240
00:16:25,972 --> 00:16:27,672
The riot police?

241
00:16:30,872 --> 00:16:32,272
Why?

242
00:16:32,272 --> 00:16:36,172
Come to think of it, something happened on the floor above.

243
00:16:36,172 --> 00:16:41,172
People were shouting that the elevator wouldn't stop on it.

244
00:16:41,172 --> 00:16:44,572
If so, I'm sure that the man with the burn is Shu!

245
00:16:44,572 --> 00:16:45,672
What?

246
00:16:45,672 --> 00:16:51,272
Look! This is a message that the man with the burn secretly gave me.

247
00:16:51,272 --> 00:16:52,972
What?

248
00:16:52,972 --> 00:16:55,972
Then, Mr. Akai somehow found out beforehand

249
00:16:55,972 --> 00:16:58,972
that something was going to happen at this department store and...

250
00:16:58,972 --> 00:16:59,972
Yes.

251
00:16:59,972 --> 00:17:03,872
There's no doubt that he already got his memory back.

252
00:17:03,872 --> 00:17:05,872
But, what's going on?

253
00:17:05,872 --> 00:17:09,572
What on earth is going on, Shu?

254
00:17:16,372 --> 00:17:18,872
According to the torn piece of paper of the courier

255
00:17:18,872 --> 00:17:22,772
that had been peeled off, where the T-shirts were inside,

256
00:17:22,772 --> 00:17:25,972
the T-shirts that were sent 7 weeks, 6 weeks and 5 weeks ago

257
00:17:25,972 --> 00:17:29,872
were all two each,

258
00:17:29,872 --> 00:17:32,972
but for some reason the one sent 4 weeks ago,

259
00:17:32,972 --> 00:17:34,972
was just one.

260
00:17:34,972 --> 00:17:38,672
Then, 3 weeks, 2 weeks ago and last week,

261
00:17:38,672 --> 00:17:44,472
two red T-shirts were sent again.

262
00:17:44,472 --> 00:17:46,972
I wonder if there's any meaning to it?

263
00:17:46,972 --> 00:17:48,072
I wonder...

264
00:17:48,072 --> 00:17:53,172
